<promed@promedmail.org>

[The serotype of _S. enterica_ in this rather large outbreak at onset of report is not stated.

It appears that no alert or recall has yet been issued by USA governmental agencies or from Costco.

Outbreaks of human salmonellosis related to fish for eating are uncommon and are more likely to be related to contamination of the fish after they are caught. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1hiS.]
